a:17:{s:4:"name";s:8:"Panmycin";s:11:"small_descr";s:63:"Tetracycline is an antibiotic that fights bacteria in the body.";s:14:"small_descr_de";s:0:"";s:14:"small_descr_fr";s:74:"Tétracycline est un antibiotique qui combat les bactéries dans le corps.";s:14:"small_descr_es";s:71:"Tetracycline es un antibiótico que combate las bacterias en el cuerpo.";s:14:"small_descr_it";s:0:"";s:10:"full_descr";s:3951:"<p><strong>INDICATIONS</strong></p><p>Panmycin is used to treat many different bacterial infections, such as urinary tract infections, acne, gonorrhea, chlamydia, and others.</p><p><strong>INSTRUCTIONS</strong></p><p><strong></strong>Take tetracycline exactly as it was prescribed for you. Take tetracycline with a full glass of water.<br /><br />Take this medication on an empty stomach, at least 1 hour before or 2 hours after meals.<br /><br />Do not take tetracycline with milk or other dairy products, unless your doctor has told you to. Dairy products can make it harder for your body to absorb the medicine. Shake the oral suspension (liquid) well just before you measure a dose. To be sure you get the correct dose, measure the liquid with a marked measuring spoon or medicine cup, not with a regular table spoon.</p><p>Take tetracycline for the entire length of time prescribed by your doctor. Your symptoms may get better before the infection is completely treated.</p><p><strong>DOSAGE</strong></p><p><strong></strong>Take tetracycline exactly as it was prescribed for you.&nbsp;If you missed a dose, take the missed dose as soon as you remember. If it is almost time for your next dose, skip the missed dose and take the medicine at the next regularly scheduled time.</p><p><strong>STORAGE</strong></p><p><strong></strong>Store this medication at room temperature away from moisture and heat.</p><p><strong>SAFETY INFORMATION</strong></p><p>Do not use tetracycline if you are pregnant. It could cause harm to the unborn baby.&nbsp;Do not take this medication without telling your doctor if you are breast-feeding a baby.</p>
<p>Tetracycline can make birth control pills less effective.</p>
<p>Do not use this medication if you are allergic to tetracycline, or to similar medicines such as demeclocycline (Declomycin), doxycycline (Adoxa, Doryx, Oracea, Vibramycin), or minocycline (Dynacin, Minocin, Solodyn, Vectrin). Before taking tetracycline, tell your doctor if you have liver or kidney disease.</p>
<p>Before taking tetracycline, tell your doctor if you are taking any of the following drugs:<br /><br />cholesterol-lowering medications such as cholestyramine (Prevalite, Questran) or colestipol (Colestid);<br />isotretinoin (Accutane);<br />tretinoin (Renova, Retin-A, Vesanoid);<br />an antacid such as Tums, Rolaids, Milk of Magnesia, Maalox, and others;<br />a product that contains bismuth subsalicylate such as Pepto-Bismol;<br />minerals such as iron, zinc, calcium, magnesium, and over-the-counter vitamin and mineral supplements;<br />a blood thinner such as warfarin (Coumadin); or<br />a penicillin antibiotic such as amoxicillin (Amoxil, Trimox, others), penicillin (BeePen-VK, Pen-Vee K, Veetids, others), dicloxacillin (Dynapen), carbenicillin (Geocillin), oxacillin (Bactocill), and others.</p><p><strong>SIDE EFFECTS</strong></p><p>Get emergency medical help if you have any of these signs of an allergic reaction: hives; difficulty breathing; swelling of your face, lips, tongue, or throat. Stop using tetracycline and call your doctor at once if you have any of these serious side effects:<br /><br />severe headache, dizziness, blurred vision;<br />fever, chills, body aches, flu symptoms;<br />severe blistering, peeling, and red skin rash;<br />urinating less than usual or not at all;<br />pale or yellowed skin, dark colored urine, fever, confusion or weakness;<br />severe pain in your upper stomach spreading to your back, nausea and vomiting, fast heart rate;<br />loss of appetite, jaundice (yellowing of the skin or eyes); or<br />easy bruising or bleeding, unusual weakness.<br /><br />Less serious tetracycline side effects may include:<br /><br />sores or swelling in your rectal or genital area;<br />mild nausea, vomiting, diarrhea, or stomach upset;<br />white patches or sores inside your mouth or on your lips;<br />swollen tongue, trouble swallowing; or<br />vaginal itching or discharge.</p>";s:13:"full_descr_de";s:0:"";s:13:"full_descr_fr";s:5336:"<p><strong>INDICATIONS</strong></p><p>Panmycin est utilis&eacute; pour traiter plusieurs infections bact&eacute;riennes, telles que les infections des voies urinaires, l'acn&eacute;, la gonorrh&eacute;e, la chlamydia, et autres.</p><p><strong><strong><strong>INSTRUCTIONS</strong></strong></strong></p><p>Prenez la t&eacute;tracycline exactement comme il a &eacute;t&eacute; prescrit pour vous. Prenez la t&eacute;tracycline avec un grand verre d'eau.<br /><br />Prenez ce m&eacute;dicament sur ​​un estomac vide, au moins 1 heure avant ou 2 heures apr&egrave;s le repas.</p><p>Ne prenez pas la t&eacute;tracycline avec du lait ou d'autres produits laitiers, sauf si votre m&eacute;decin vous a dit. Les produits laitiers peuvent rendre plus difficile pour votre corps d'absorber le m&eacute;dicament. Agitez la suspension buvable (liquide) avant de mesurer la dose. Pour &ecirc;tre s&ucirc;r d'obtenir la dose correcte, mesurez le liquide avec une cuill&egrave;re-mesure marqu&eacute;e ou une tasse de m&eacute;decine, pas avec une cuill&egrave;re de table ordinaire.</p><p>Prenez la t&eacute;tracycline pendant toute la dur&eacute;e du d&eacute;lai prescrit par votre m&eacute;decin. Vos sympt&ocirc;mes peuvent s'am&eacute;liorer avant que l'infection ne soit compl&egrave;tement trait&eacute;e.</p><p><strong><strong>DOSAGE</strong></strong></p><p>Prenez la t&eacute;tracycline exactement comme il a &eacute;t&eacute; prescrit pour vous.&nbsp;Si vous avez manqu&eacute; une dose, prenez la dose manqu&eacute;e aussit&ocirc;t que vous vous souvenez. S'il est presque temps pour votre prochaine dose, sautez la dose oubli&eacute;e et prendre le m&eacute;dicament &agrave; la prochaine heure r&eacute;guli&egrave;re.</p><p><strong><strong>CONSERVATION</strong></strong></p><p><strong><strong></strong></strong>Conservez ce m&eacute;dicament &agrave; la temp&eacute;rature ambiante loin de l'humidit&eacute; et de la chaleur.</p><p><strong>RENSEIGNEMENTS DE SÉCURITÉ</strong></p><p>N'utilisez pas la t&eacute;tracycline si vous &ecirc;tes enceinte. Cela pourrait causer des dommages au b&eacute;b&eacute; &agrave; na&icirc;tre. Ne prenez pas ce m&eacute;dicament sans en parler &agrave; votre m&eacute;decin si vous allaitez un b&eacute;b&eacute;.<br /><br />T&eacute;tracycline peut faire la pilule contraceptive moins efficace.</p>
<p>N'utilisez pas ce m&eacute;dicament si vous &ecirc;tes allergique &agrave; la t&eacute;tracycline ou aux m&eacute;dicaments similaires tels que demeclocycline (Declomycin), la doxycycline (Adoxa, Doryx, Oracea, doxycycline), ou la minocycline (Dynacin, Minocin, Solodyn, Vectrin). Avant de prendre la t&eacute;tracycline, pr&eacute;venez votre m&eacute;decin si vous avez une maladie h&eacute;patique ou r&eacute;nale.</p>
<p>Avant de prendre la t&eacute;tracycline, pr&eacute;venez votre m&eacute;decin si vous prenez l'un des m&eacute;dicaments suivants:<br /><br />m&eacute;dicaments anti-cholest&eacute;rol comme la cholestyramine (Prevalite, Questran) ou colestipol (Colestid);<br />isotr&eacute;tino&iuml;ne (Accutane);<br />tr&eacute;tino&iuml;ne (Renova, Retin-A, Vesanoid);<br />un antiacide tel que Tums, Rolaids, Lait de Magn&eacute;sie, Maalox et d'autres;<br />un produit qui contient le bismuth subsalicylate tel que Pepto-Bismol;<br />des min&eacute;raux tels que le fer, le zinc, le calcium, le magn&eacute;sium, et sur ​​le comptoir de suppl&eacute;ments vitaminiques et min&eacute;raux;<br />un diluant du sang comme la warfarine (Coumadin); ou<br />un antibiotique de p&eacute;nicilline comme l'amoxicilline (Amoxil, Trimox, autres), la p&eacute;nicilline (BeePen-VK, Pen-Vee K, Veetids, autres), dicloxacillin (Dynapen), carbenicilline (Geocillin), oxacilline (Bactocill), et d'autres.</p><p><strong>LES EFFETS SECONDAIRES</strong></p><p>Obtenez de l'aide m&eacute;dicale d'urgence si vous avez un de ces signes d'une r&eacute;action allergique: urticaire, difficult&eacute;s respiratoires, gonflement du visage, des l&egrave;vres, de la langue ou de la gorge. Cessez d'utiliser la t&eacute;tracycline et appelez votre m&eacute;decin imm&eacute;diatement si vous avez un de ces effets secondaires s&eacute;rieux:<br /><br />maux de t&ecirc;te violents, des vertiges, vision floue;<br />la fi&egrave;vre, des frissons, des courbatures, des sympt&ocirc;mes de grippe;<br />cloques graves, peeling, et une &eacute;ruption cutan&eacute;e rouge;<br />uriner moins que d'habitude ou pas du tout;<br />peau p&acirc;le ou jaunes, urines fonc&eacute;es, fi&egrave;vre, confusion ou une faiblesse;<br />la douleur s&eacute;v&egrave;re dans votre estomac sup&eacute;rieure propagation &agrave; votre dos, des naus&eacute;es et des vomissements, acc&eacute;l&eacute;ration du rythme cardiaque;<br />perte d'app&eacute;tit, jaunisse (jaunissement de la peau ou des yeux); ou<br />ecchymoses ou des saignements, faiblesse inhabituelle.</p>
<p>Effets secondaires de t&eacute;tracycline moins graves peuvent inclure:<br /><br />plaies ou se gonflant dans ta r&eacute;gion rectale ou g&eacute;nitale;<br />naus&eacute;es, des vomissements, la diarrh&eacute;e ou des maux d'estomac;<br />correctifs ou des plaies dans votre bouche ou sur vos l&egrave;vres blanches;<br />gonflement de la langue, difficult&eacute; &agrave; avaler, ou<br />d&eacute;mangeaisons ou pertes vaginales.</p>";s:13:"full_descr_es";s:4659:"<p><strong><strong>INDICACIONES</strong></strong></p><p>Panmycin es utilizado para tratar muchos tipos de infecciones bacterianas, como las infecciones del tracto urinario, el acn&eacute;, la gonorrea, la clamidia, y otras.</p><p><strong>INSTRUCCIONES</strong></p><p>Tome tetracycline exactamente como su m&eacute;dico ha recetado. Tome tetracycline con un vaso lleno de agua.<br /><br />Tome este medicamento con el est&oacute;mago vac&iacute;o, al menos 1 hora antes o 2 horas despu&eacute;s de la comida.</p><p>No tome tetracycline con leche o otros productos l&aacute;cteos, a menos que su m&eacute;dico ha indicado a hacerlo. Los productos l&aacute;cteos pueden hacer m&aacute;s dif&iacute;cil para su cuerpo de absorber el medicamento. Agite bien la suspensi&oacute;n oral (l&iacute;quido) antes de medir una dosis. Para ser seguro que recibe la dosis correcta, mida el l&iacute;quido con una cuchara o taza para medir medicina, y no con una cuchara regular de mesa.</p><p>Tome tetracycline durante todo el tiempo recetado por su m&eacute;dico. Sus s&iacute;ntomas pueden mejorar antes de que la infecci&oacute;n est&eacute; completamente curada.</p><p><strong>DOSIS</strong></p><p>Tome tetracycline exactamente como su m&eacute;dico ha recetado.&nbsp;Si Usted ha omitido una dosis, tome la dosis olvidada tan pronto como lo recuerde. Si es casi la hora de su pr&oacute;xima dosis, omita la dosis olvidada y tome la medicina a la pr&oacute;xima hora regularmente programada.</p><p><strong>ALMACENAMIENTO</strong></p><p><strong></strong>Almacene esta medicina a temperatura ambiente lejos de la humedad y el calor.</p><p><strong>INFORMACIÓN DE SEGURIDAD</strong></p><p>No use tetracycline, si Usted est&aacute; embarazada. Esta medicina puede causar da&ntilde;o al beb&eacute; nonato. No tome este medicamento sin antes decirle a su m&eacute;dico si amamanta un beb&eacute;.<br /><br />Tetracycline puede hacer las pastillas anticonceptivas menos efectivas.</p>
<p>No use esta medicina si Usted es al&eacute;rgico a tetracycline o medicamentos similares, como demeclociclina (Declomycin), doxiciclina (Adoxa, Doryx, Oracea, Vibramycin),&nbsp;o minociclina (Dynacin Minocin, Solodyn, Vectrin). Antes de tomar tetracycline, d&iacute;ga a su m&eacute;dico si Usted tiene enfermedad del h&iacute;gado o ri&ntilde;&oacute;n.</p>
<p>Antes de tomar tetracycline, d&iacute;ce a su m&eacute;dico si Usted est&aacute; tomando alguna de las drogas siguientes:<br /><br />medicamentos para bajar el colesterol como colestiramina (Prevalite, Questran) o colestipol (Colestid);<br />isotretino&iacute;na (Accutane);<br />tretino&iacute;na (Renova, Retin-A, Vesanoid);<br />anti&aacute;cido, como Tums, Rolaids, Leche de Magnesia, Maalox, y otros;<br />un producto que contiene salicilato de bismuto como Pepto-Bismol;<br />minerales tales como hierro, zinc, calcio, magnesio, y suplementos minerales de venta libre y vitamina;<br />un anticoagulante como la warfarina (Coumadin), o<br />un antibi&oacute;tico de penicilina como amoxicillin (Amoxil, Trimox, otras), penicilina (BeePen-VK, Pen-Vee K, Veetids, otros), dicloxacilina (Dynapen), carbenicilina (Geocillin), oxacilina (Bactocill), y otros.</p><p><strong>EFECTOS SECUNDARIOS</strong></p><p>Busque atenci&oacute;n m&eacute;dica de emergencia si usted tiene alguno de estos s&iacute;ntomas de una reacci&oacute;n al&eacute;rgica: ronchas, dificultad para respirar, hinchaz&oacute;n de la cara, labios, lengua, o garganta. Deje de usar tetracycline y llame a su m&eacute;dico inmediatamente si usted tiene alguno de estos efectos secundarios graves:<br /><br />dolor de cabeza severo, mareo, visi&oacute;n borrosa;<br />fiebre, escalofr&iacute;os, dolor del cuerpo, s&iacute;ntomas de la influenza;<br />ampollas, descamaci&oacute;n, y sarpullido rojo;<br />orinar menos de lo usual o nada en absoluto;<br />piel p&aacute;lida o amarilla, orina oscura, fiebre, confusi&oacute;n o debilidad;<br />dolor severo en su est&oacute;mago que se extiende a su espalda, n&aacute;usea y v&oacute;mito, paso card&iacute;aco r&aacute;pido;<br />p&eacute;rdida de apetito, ictericia (coloraci&oacute;n amarillenta de la piel o los ojos), o<br />f&aacute;cil aparici&oacute;n de moretones o sangrado, debilidad inusual.</p>
<p>Efectos secundarios tetracycline menos serios pueden incluir:<br /><br />llagas o hinchaz&oacute;n en el &aacute;rea rectal o genital;<br />n&aacute;usea leve, malestar estomacal, v&oacute;mitos, diarrea o malestar estomacal;<br />manchas blancas o llagas dentro de la boca o en sus labios;<br />inflamaci&oacute;n de la lengua, dificultad para tragar, o<br />Picaz&oacute;n o flujo vaginal.</p>";s:13:"full_descr_it";s:0:"";s:9:"min_price";s:8:"0.640332";s:9:"pack_name";s:5:"pills";s:4:"type";s:2:"mg";s:7:"analogs";a:3:{s:12:"Tetracycline";s:11:"Antibiotics";s:7:"Sumycin";s:11:"Antibiotics";s:10:"Terramycin";s:11:"Antibiotics";}s:18:"active_ingredients";N;s:8:"packings";a:2:{i:500;a:8:{i:6493;a:5:{s:10:"id_packing";s:4:"6493";s:5:"count";s:2:"20";s:6:"dosage";d:500;s:14:"price_per_pill";s:7:"2.08392";s:4:"name";s:8:"Panmycin";}i:6494;a:5:{s:10:"id_packing";s:4:"6494";s:5:"count";s:2:"30";s:6:"dosage";d:500;s:14:"price_per_pill";s:7:"1.60584";s:4:"name";s:8:"Panmycin";}i:6495;a:5:{s:10:"id_packing";s:4:"6495";s:5:"count";s:2:"60";s:6:"dosage";d:500;s:14:"price_per_pill";s:7:"1.12777";s:4:"name";s:8:"Panmycin";}i:6496;a:5:{s:10:"id_packing";s:4:"6496";s:5:"count";s:2:"90";s:6:"dosage";d:500;s:14:"price_per_pill";s:7:"0.96841";s:4:"name";s:8:"Panmycin";}i:6497;a:5:{s:10:"id_packing";s:4:"6497";s:5:"count";s:3:"120";s:6:"dosage";d:500;s:14:"price_per_pill";s:7:"0.88873";s:4:"name";s:8:"Panmycin";}i:6498;a:5:{s:10:"id_packing";s:4:"6498";s:5:"count";s:3:"180";s:6:"dosage";d:500;s:14:"price_per_pill";s:7:"0.80905";s:4:"name";s:8:"Panmycin";}i:6499;a:5:{s:10:"id_packing";s:4:"6499";s:5:"count";s:3:"270";s:6:"dosage";d:500;s:14:"price_per_pill";s:7:"0.75593";s:4:"name";s:8:"Panmycin";}i:6500;a:5:{s:10:"id_packing";s:4:"6500";s:5:"count";s:3:"360";s:6:"dosage";d:500;s:14:"price_per_pill";s:7:"0.72937";s:4:"name";s:8:"Panmycin";}}i:250;a:8:{i:6501;a:5:{s:10:"id_packing";s:4:"6501";s:5:"count";s:2:"20";s:6:"dosage";d:250;s:14:"price_per_pill";s:6:"1.7787";s:4:"name";s:8:"Panmycin";}i:6502;a:5:{s:10:"id_packing";s:4:"6502";s:5:"count";s:2:"30";s:6:"dosage";d:250;s:14:"price_per_pill";s:7:"1.37692";s:4:"name";s:8:"Panmycin";}i:6503;a:5:{s:10:"id_packing";s:4:"6503";s:5:"count";s:2:"60";s:6:"dosage";d:250;s:14:"price_per_pill";s:7:"0.97515";s:4:"name";s:8:"Panmycin";}i:6504;a:5:{s:10:"id_packing";s:4:"6504";s:5:"count";s:2:"90";s:6:"dosage";d:250;s:14:"price_per_pill";s:7:"0.84122";s:4:"name";s:8:"Panmycin";}i:6505;a:5:{s:10:"id_packing";s:4:"6505";s:5:"count";s:3:"120";s:6:"dosage";d:250;s:14:"price_per_pill";s:7:"0.77426";s:4:"name";s:8:"Panmycin";}i:6506;a:5:{s:10:"id_packing";s:4:"6506";s:5:"count";s:3:"180";s:6:"dosage";d:250;s:14:"price_per_pill";s:7:"0.70729";s:4:"name";s:8:"Panmycin";}i:6507;a:5:{s:10:"id_packing";s:4:"6507";s:5:"count";s:3:"270";s:6:"dosage";d:250;s:14:"price_per_pill";s:7:"0.66265";s:4:"name";s:8:"Panmycin";}i:6508;a:5:{s:10:"id_packing";s:4:"6508";s:5:"count";s:3:"360";s:6:"dosage";d:250;s:14:"price_per_pill";s:7:"0.64033";s:4:"name";s:8:"Panmycin";}}}}